{
  "text": "The incidence of breast cancer was significantly higher among patients receiving thyroid hormone in comparison to control patients. The risk increased with duration of use, being almost 20% in those receiving it for more than 15 years. The risk was more than three-fold higher in nulliparous women receiving thyroid hormone, reaching 33%, whereas it was only 9.25% in those not receiving thyroid hormone [CITATION_1] .",
